    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. i'm seeing a lot of debate online about whether it's actually a legitimate legal method or if it's just used as a cover for conservative politics. how do scholars distinguish between a \"principled\" use of originalism and just using it as a tool to reach a specific political outcome?",
